etymologies: late 19th century. From scientific Latin Dicyema, genus name + -id

definitions: Any microscopic worm of the rhombozoan group Dicyemida, having a complicated life cycle with two kinds of larvae.

notes.text: The Dicyemida have been treated as an order of the phylum Mesozoa or of the phylum Rhombozoa. The name is now frequently regarded as a preferred synonym of the phylum Rhombozoa.
